description:
&lt;h1&gt;IT Development Consultant&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;A digital Patient Health Record (&lt;span&gt;PHR&lt;/span&gt;) is crucial to allow patients to view and manage their own health record. You will be a key team player in developing a &lt;span&gt;PHR&lt;/span&gt; for Portsmouth Hospital University Trust. You will be responsible for working as part of a Scrum team who develop web and integration solutions that enable information sharing between clinical and corporate systems. Your work will directly impact day to day patient care&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The team currently uses Visual Studio 2019, &lt;span&gt;SQL&lt;/span&gt; Server 2012/2016 and .NET. We are in the initial stages of building a suite of micro services in order to better facilitate availability of information across our various applications and help ramp up our development and deployment capability.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We also carry out healthcare integration work on our Health Connect platform, using standard healthcare protocols such as HL7 and &lt;span&gt;ITK&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will have the opportunity to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Design, develop, and deliver new features on our in-house solutions&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Influence our technical design strategy&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lead on some of our products&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Collaborate with our multidisciplinary Scrum team&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Assist in requirements identification and producing specifications&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Support the creation and maintenance of technical documentation&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Contribute and adhere to coding standards, best practices, and procedures&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Assist and mentor junior team members&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ideal candidates:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Fluent in English and C#&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Experience developing web applications using ASP.NET &lt;span&gt;MVC&lt;/span&gt;, ASP.NET Core, &lt;span&gt;WebApi&lt;/span&gt;, JavaScript and Angular&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Experience with &lt;span&gt;LINQ&lt;/span&gt; &amp; Entity Framework, &lt;span&gt;SQL&lt;/span&gt; Server and T-&lt;span&gt;SQL&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Enjoy learning new skills and finding the best tools for the job&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Knowledge and application of enterprise software design patterns including &lt;span&gt;SOA&lt;/span&gt; and micro services&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Practical knowledge of &lt;span&gt;OOP&lt;/span&gt; concepts and SOLID principles&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Understanding of HTTP and &lt;span&gt;RESTful&lt;/span&gt; design&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience of using Health Connect integration platform and knowledge of HL7 protocols&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience with Unit and Integration testing&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience with Continuous Integration and Deployment work flows&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ability to interact effectively with multidisciplinary teams&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Proven history of successful software development&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Exceptional attention to detail&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience in automated testing&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What can we offer you?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Deep working atmosphere&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Access to &lt;span&gt;Pluralsight&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Career progression&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Flexible working&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Home working&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The chance to work in an experienced software development team that takes pride in their work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Staff benefits which include excellent pension scheme, childcare vouchers, gym / swimming pool membership, cycle to work scheme, access to our beach hut and many more!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Department:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The IT department has 70+ staff with a broad range of skills and experiences. We pride ourselves on our culture of &lt;span&gt;‘working&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span&gt;together’&lt;/span&gt; for the benefit of patients. The IT department is located less than a mile from &lt;span&gt;Fratton&lt;/span&gt; train station, in a recently refurbished building with great facilities and free parking. The adjacent retail park includes a number of fast food restaurants, a supermarket and several gyms.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a great opportunity for someone with the right attitude to gain a wealth of new experience and have a positive impact on the local community that we serve.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Closing Date 26/11/20&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
